---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="New Construction Plumber in Tacoma, WA | Daley Plumbing"
  description="From rough-in to final trim, Daley Plumbing handles every phase of new construction plumbing in Pierce and King County. On time, on code, on budget. Call (224) 430-1420"
>
  <Header />
  <main>
    <!-- Hero -->
    <section class="pt-28 md:pt-36 pb-16 bg-primary text-white">
      <div class="container mx-auto px-4 text-center">
        <p class="text-white/60 uppercase tracking-widest text-sm mb-4">Our Flagship Service</p>
        <h1 class="font-display text-5xl md:text-7xl mb-4">New Construction Plumbing in the South Sound</h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-white/80 max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-8">
          Built Right from Day One
        </p>
        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-center justify-center gap-4">
          <a href="tel:2244301420" class="inline-flex items-center gap-3 bg-white text-primary px-8 py-4 font-semibold hover:bg-secondary transition-all">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path d="M6.62 10.79c1.44 2.83 3.76 5.14 6.59 6.59l2.2-2.2c.27-.27.67-.36 1.02-.24 1.12.37 2.33.57 3.57.57.55 0 1 .45 1 1V20c0 .55-.45 1-1 1-9.39 0-17-7.61-17-17 0-.55.45-1 1-1h3.5c.55 0 1 .45 1 1 0 1.25.2 2.45.57 3.57.11.35.03.74-.25 1.02l-2.2 2.2z"/>
            </svg>
            Call (224) 430-1420
          </a>
          <a href="#cta-form" class="inline-block border-2 border-white/80 text-white px-8 py-4 font-semibold hover:bg-white hover:text-primary transition-all">
            Work With Us on Your Next Build
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Intro -->
    <section class="py-20 bg-secondary">
      <div class="container mx-auto px-4">
        <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
          <p class="text-xl text-neutral-800 leading-relaxed mb-6">
            From rough-in to final trim, Daley Plumbing handles every phase of new construction plumbing in Pierce and King County. We work with builders, contractors, and homeowners to keep projects on schedule and up to code — with the kind of communication that makes a job site actually run smoothly.
          </p>
          <p class="text-lg text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed">
            New construction is where we got our start, and it's still where we do our best work. We've plumbed everything from single-family homes to multi-unit developments. We know the permitting process, we know the inspection requirements, and we know what it takes to get the job done without holding up your schedule.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Phases -->
    <section class="py-20 bg-white">
      <div class="container mx-auto px-4">
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
          <div class="text-center mb-16">
            <h2 class="font-display text-4xl md:text-5xl text-primary mb-4">How New Construction Plumbing Works</h2>
            <p class="text-lg text-neutral-600">Three phases, one standard: do it right.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="space-y-8">
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-[auto_1fr] gap-6 items-start">
              <div class="w-16 h-16 bg-primary text-white flex items-center justify-center font-display text-3xl flex-shrink-0">1</div>
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-display text-3xl text-primary mb-2">Rough-In</h3>
                <p class="text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed">
                  The first phase — running all drain, waste, and vent pipes through the framing before walls close up. This is the foundation of the entire plumbing system. It requires precise layout, careful slope calculations, and a passed inspection before the project moves forward. We get it right the first time.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="border-t border-neutral-200"></div>

            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-[auto_1fr] gap-6 items-start">
              <div class="w-16 h-16 bg-primary text-white flex items-center justify-center font-display text-3xl flex-shrink-0">2</div>
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-display text-3xl text-primary mb-2">Top-Out</h3>
                <p class="text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed">
                  Also called above-slab work. This phase involves roughing in venting and drain lines above the slab or sub-floor. Vent stacks go through the roof, supply lines are run to each fixture location, and everything is tested and pressure-checked. It's the guts of the system — invisible once the walls go up, but critical to how everything performs.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="border-t border-neutral-200"></div>

            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-[auto_1fr] gap-6 items-start">
              <div class="w-16 h-16 bg-primary text-white flex items-center justify-center font-display text-3xl flex-shrink-0">3</div>
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-display text-3xl text-primary mb-2">Trim / Finish</h3>
                <p class="text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed">
                  The final phase — installing all the visible fixtures once the walls, floors, and countertops are in. Sinks, faucets, toilets, water heaters, dishwasher lines, supply connections, the works. This is where the homeowner sees the finished product, so we make sure everything looks as good as it works.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Contractor Section -->
    <section class="py-20 bg-gradient-to-br from-secondary via-white to-tan/30">
      <div class="container mx-auto px-4">
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
          <div>
            <h2 class="font-display text-4xl md:text-5xl text-primary mb-6">Working With a Builder?</h2>
            <p class="text-lg text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
              We know how job sites work. We show up on time, communicate clearly with your GC and subs, and don't hold up your schedule. No chasing us down for updates — we keep you in the loop because that's how good projects get built.
            </p>
            <p class="text-lg text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
              Ask about contractor rates for ongoing projects — one good relationship is worth more than a hundred one-off calls.
            </p>
            <a href="#cta-form" class="inline-block bg-primary text-white px-8 py-4 font-semibold hover:bg-primary/90 transition-all">
              Ask About Contractor Rates
            </a>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white p-8 shadow-sm border-l-4 border-primary">
            <h3 class="font-display text-2xl text-primary mb-4">What Contractors Get</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-3 text-neutral-700">
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-green flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd"/></svg>
                On-time arrivals that don't hold up your schedule
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-green flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd"/></svg>
                Clean communication with your team and other subs
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-green flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd"/></svg>
                Pierce County permit process expertise
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-green flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd"/></svg>
                Inspections passed the first time
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-green flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd"/></svg>
                Competitive rates for ongoing partnerships
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Cities Served -->
    <section class="py-16 bg-white">
      <div class="container mx-auto px-4 text-center">
        <h2 class="font-display text-3xl md:text-4xl text-primary mb-8">New Construction Plumbing Across the South Sound</h2>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-3 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
          {['Tacoma', 'Federal Way', 'Puyallup', 'Lakewood', 'Gig Harbor', 'Bonney Lake', 'Spanaway', 'University Place', 'Fife', 'Sumner', 'Auburn', 'Milton', 'Edgewood'].map(city => (
            <span class="bg-secondary px-4 py-2 text-neutral-700 font-medium border border-neutral-200">{city}</span>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- FAQ -->
    <section class="py-20 bg-gradient-to-br from-secondary via-white to-tan/30">
      <div class="container mx-auto px-4">
        <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
          <h2 class="font-display text-4xl md:text-5xl text-primary mb-12 text-center">Common Questions</h2>

          <div class="space-y-6">
            <details class="bg-white p-6 shadow-sm border-l-4 border-primary group" open>
              <summary class="font-display text-xl text-primary cursor-pointer flex items-center justify-between">
                How much does new construction plumbing cost in Tacoma?
                <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-primary transform group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
              </summary>
              <p class="text-neutral-700 mt-4 leading-relaxed">
                Cost depends on the size of the home, number of fixtures, and complexity of the layout. A typical single-family home in Pierce County can range from $8,000–$15,000+ for a full plumbing package (rough-in through trim). We'll give you a detailed quote upfront — no ballpark-and-hope pricing.
              </p>
            </details>

            <details class="bg-white p-6 shadow-sm border-l-4 border-primary group">
              <summary class="font-display text-xl text-primary cursor-pointer flex items-center justify-between">
                What permits do I need for plumbing in Pierce County?
                <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-primary transform group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
              </summary>
              <p class="text-neutral-700 mt-4 leading-relaxed">
                New construction plumbing in Pierce County requires a plumbing permit through Pierce County Planning and Public Works. We handle the permit process as part of our scope — pulling the permit, scheduling inspections, and making sure everything passes. One less thing for you (or your GC) to think about.
              </p>
            </details>

            <details class="bg-white p-6 shadow-sm border-l-4 border-primary group">
              <summary class="font-display text-xl text-primary cursor-pointer flex items-center justify-between">
                How long does new construction plumbing take?
                <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-primary transform group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
              </summary>
              <p class="text-neutral-700 mt-4 leading-relaxed">
                For a standard single-family home, rough-in typically takes 2–4 days, top-out is 1–2 days, and trim is 1–2 days. Total plumbing time spread across the build schedule is usually 5–8 working days. We coordinate with your GC to fit within the overall construction timeline without delays.
              </p>
            </details>

            <details class="bg-white p-6 shadow-sm border-l-4 border-primary group">
              <summary class="font-display text-xl text-primary cursor-pointer flex items-center justify-between">
                What is rough-in plumbing?
                <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-primary transform group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
              </summary>
              <p class="text-neutral-700 mt-4 leading-relaxed">
                Rough-in is the first phase of new construction plumbing. It's when all the drain, waste, vent, and supply pipes are installed inside the walls and floors — before drywall goes up. It has to be done precisely and pass inspection before the build can continue. This is the part most homeowners never see, but it's the most important phase of the entire system.
              </p>
            </details>

            <details class="bg-white p-6 shadow-sm border-l-4 border-primary group">
              <summary class="font-display text-xl text-primary cursor-pointer flex items-center justify-between">
                Do you work with homeowners or just contractors?
                <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-primary transform group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
              </summary>
              <p class="text-neutral-700 mt-4 leading-relaxed">
                Both. We work directly with homeowners who are owner-building, and we partner with general contractors and builders on larger projects. Either way, you get the same level of communication and quality. We speak both languages.
              </p>
            </details>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CTA Form -->
    <section id="cta-form" class="py-20 bg-primary text-white">
      <div class="container mx-auto px-4">
        <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto">
          <div class="text-center mb-10">
            <h2 class="font-display text-4xl md:text-5xl mb-4">Work With Us on Your Next Build</h2>
            <p class="text-white/70">Tell us about your project. No obligation.</p>
          </div>
          <!-- Wire this form to Netlify Forms, Formspree, or your preferred handler -->
          <form class="space-y-5" name="new-construction" method="POST">
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-5">
              <div>
                <label for="nc-name" class="block text-sm font-medium text-white/80 mb-2">Name</label>
                <input type="text" id="nc-name" name="name" required class="w-full px-4 py-3 bg-white/10 border border-white/30 text-white placeholder-white/50 focus:border-white focus:ring-2 focus:ring-white/20 outline-none transition-all" placeholder="Your name" />
              </div>
              <div>
                <label for="nc-phone" class="block text-sm font-medium text-white/80 mb-2">Phone</label>
                <input type="tel" id="nc-phone" name="phone" required class="w-full px-4 py-3 bg-white/10 border border-white/30 text-white placeholder-white/50 focus:border-white focus:ring-2 focus:ring-white/20 outline-none transition-all" placeholder="(253) 555-0000" />
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-5">
              <div>
                <label for="nc-email" class="block text-sm font-medium text-white/80 mb-2">Email</label>
                <input type="email" id="nc-email" name="email" class="w-full px-4 py-3 bg-white/10 border border-white/30 text-white placeholder-white/50 focus:border-white focus:ring-2 focus:ring-white/20 outline-none transition-all" placeholder="your@email.com" />
              </div>
              <div>
                <label for="nc-city" class="block text-sm font-medium text-white/80 mb-2">Project City</label>
                <select id="nc-city" name="city" class="w-full px-4 py-3 bg-white/10 border border-white/30 text-white focus:border-white focus:ring-2 focus:ring-white/20 outline-none transition-all">
                  <option value="" class="text-neutral-800">Select city...</option>
                  <option value="tacoma" class="text-neutral-800">Tacoma</option>
                  <option value="federal-way" class="text-neutral-800">Federal Way</option>
                  <option value="puyallup" class="text-neutral-800">Puyallup</option>
                  <option value="lakewood" class="text-neutral-800">Lakewood</option>
                  <option value="gig-harbor" class="text-neutral-800">Gig Harbor</option>
                  <option value="bonney-lake" class="text-neutral-800">Bonney Lake</option>
                  <option value="sumner" class="text-neutral-800">Sumner</option>
                  <option value="other" class="text-neutral-800">Other</option>
                </select>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-5">
              <div>
                <label for="nc-type" class="block text-sm font-medium text-white/80 mb-2">Project Type</label>
                <select id="nc-type" name="project-type" class="w-full px-4 py-3 bg-white/10 border border-white/30 text-white focus:border-white focus:ring-2 focus:ring-white/20 outline-none transition-all">
                  <option value="" class="text-neutral-800">Select type...</option>
                  <option value="single-family" class="text-neutral-800">Single-Family Home</option>
                  <option value="multi-family" class="text-neutral-800">Multi-Family / Duplex</option>
                  <option value="commercial" class="text-neutral-800">Commercial</option>
                  <option value="other" class="text-neutral-800">Other</option>
                </select>
              </div>
              <div>
                <label for="nc-timeline" class="block text-sm font-medium text-white/80 mb-2">Timeline</label>
                <select id="nc-timeline" name="timeline" class="w-full px-4 py-3 bg-white/10 border border-white/30 text-white focus:border-white focus:ring-2 focus:ring-white/20 outline-none transition-all">
                  <option value="" class="text-neutral-800">When do you need us?</option>
                  <option value="asap" class="text-neutral-800">ASAP</option>
                  <option value="1-month" class="text-neutral-800">Within 1 month</option>
                  <option value="1-3-months" class="text-neutral-800">1–3 months</option>
                  <option value="3-plus" class="text-neutral-800">3+ months out</option>
                  <option value="planning" class="text-neutral-800">Still planning</option>
                </select>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div>
              <label for="nc-details" class="block text-sm font-medium text-white/80 mb-2">Project Details</label>
              <textarea id="nc-details" name="details" rows="4" class="w-full px-4 py-3 bg-white/10 border border-white/30 text-white placeholder-white/50 focus:border-white focus:ring-2 focus:ring-white/20 outline-none transition-all resize-none" placeholder="Tell us about the build — size, phase, anything helpful..."></textarea>
            </div>
            <button type="submit" class="w-full bg-accent text-white px-6 py-4 font-semibold text-lg hover:bg-accent/90 transition-colors">
              Request a Quote — No Pressure
            </button>
          </form>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>
